Version 0.7.0
	Fix critical bug in identifing CHG and CHH methylation. All versions from 0.6.7 likely affected.
	Remove failed sort output files to allow for more automated recovery.
	Keep old logfile if recovering from temporary files.

Version 0.6.9
	Bugfix on number of sorted files created.

Version 0.6.8
	Bowtie(2) processing now writes to multiple files, split by chromosome, strand, context, and 10^7 bases. This reduces the difficulty of sort and allows it to be moved back into temporary filespace.

Version 0.6.7
	Moved all the work into subroutines, recovery from temporary files smoother, added parallelisation and memory options to sort.

Version 0.6.6
	Sorting moved into temporary directory specified by user to prevent swap space running out.

Version 0.6.5
	First public release of YAMA.
